creator: Nabta Health
descriptionHtml:
Nabta: Woman-shaped healthcare. Empowering women to manage their health and blossom at all ages. Download for FREE today!

Manage your health in one place with the support of your AI-powered personal health assistant, Aya, on the Nabta app. Choose from one of four modes to achieve your goals: Get Fit & Healthy, Track My Cycle, Monitor My Pregnancy, Prepare For Menopause.

Access mode-specific features, support, integrated devices and tests, all housed within the Nabta app. Everything you need to live your healthiest life.

Nabta app includes four health goals, including:
Get Fit & Healthy: for women who want to lose weight, gain weight, or improve their overall levels of fitness. In this mode, Aya will prompt you to log your health data for parameters, such as, your exercise, sleep and calorie intake.

Track My Cycle: for women who want to track their periods, who are actively trying to conceive or avoid pregnancy. For women trying to get pregnant, the real-time fertility monitor integrates with this mode - an FDA-approved, CE-certified medical device - detects ovulation with 99% accuracy in-cycle, provides in-depth cycle insights regardless of your cycle length and regularity and may detect any underlying conditions that could affect ovulation.

Monitor My Pregnancy: for women who are pregnant or curious to see what pregnancy looks like. It has some great features and the ability to log all of your pregnancy symptoms. This mode gives you everything you need to prepare for your new arrival.

Prepare For Menopause: for women to take control of menopause. This mode is designed to help with the perimenopausal period, including advice on everything from HRTs to hot flashes.

Nabta Health features:

Available in English & Arabic.

AI-powered health assistant: Aya will talk you through setting up your account and defining your personal health goals. She is on hand to answer any questions, remind you to log your health data and connect you to a medical professional.

Integrated devices and tests: Aya will direct you to the tools, tests and specialist support you need to manage your health as efficiently and privately as possible. All data and results will integrate directly into your Nabta app.

Cycle tracker and predictor: track your cycle to help or avoid becoming pregnant.

Advice and education: 100s of content pieces from health specialists.

Community: join & support the Nabta community to connect with other like-minded women.

Nabta Health is designed to support women of all ages and to make the management of your health and wellbeing easier, using our interactive app. Start achieving your goals and living your healthiest life today.

title: نبتة | Nabta

creator: Nabta Health
descriptionHtml:
Your Health, Your Journey

Personalise your health journey at every age and every stage. From daily wellbeing, to fertility, pregnancy and menopause.

Manage your health in one place with the support of your AI-powered personal health assistant, Aya. And choose from one of four modes to achieve your goals:

*Get Fit & Healthy* - for women who want to lose weight, gain weight, or improve their overall levels of fitness. In this mode, Aya will prompt you to add logs that give an indication of your overall health and wellbeing, such as your exercise, sleep and calorie intake.

*Track My Cycle* - for women who are actively trying to get pregnant, or just want to track their periods and understand more about their cycles. This mode has extra features for women who are trying to get pregnant, including an integrated real-time fertility monitor that detects ovulation with up to 99% accuracy in cycle!

*Monitor My Pregnancy* - for women who are pregnant or curious to see what pregnancy looks like. This mode has some great features, including the ability to log all of your pregnancy symptoms, and gives you everything you need to prepare for your new arrival.

*Prepare For Menopause* - for women to take control of menopause. This mode is designed to help you navigate the perimenopausal period, providing advice on everything from Hormone Replacement Therapy (HRT) to hot flashes, and what you can do to alleviate some of the symptoms of menopause.

AND THERE'S MORE!

The Nabta نبتة app is:

- Available in English & Arabic.

- Offers AI-powered symptom triage and health assistance.

- Provides access to 1000s of evidence-based articles from health specialists.

- Offers support from an engaged and informed community of like-minded women.


Start achieving your goals and living your healthiest life today. And follow us on social media @NabtaHealth.

title: Nabta | نبتة - Your personal health assistant

creator: Nabta Health
descriptionHtml:
#1 HOLISTIC HEALTH TRACKING app for women in the Middle East, Africa and South Asia.

DID YOU KNOW
Your menstrual cycle is your 5th vital sign? As important for understanding your overall health as your heart rate, blood pressure, respiration rate and temperature?

SOMETHING IS WRONG
If you suffer with irregular cycles, heavy periods, painful periods, bleeding between periods, extreme PMS (known as Premenstrual Dysphoric Disorder), smelly discharge, itching, dryness – the list goes on.

GET DETAILED INSIGHTS YOU CAN TRUST
About your menstrual cycle in the context of your hormonal and overall health. The Nabta app combines the best of female, artificial and medical intelligence to help you understand your menstrual cycle in the context of your HEALTH GOALS.
• Want to know why your period is always late? We can help.
• Forced to take a sick day every month because of crippling period pain? We can help.
• Struggling to lose weight or keep it off? We can help.
• Worried you have PCOS? We can help.
• Trying to conceive for 6 months without success? We can help.

USE THE APP DAILY
The Nabta app is free and easy to use. It is designed to become a discreet, yet dependable part of your life, helping you manage your health with daily monitoring and advice. We use the most secure data encryption, ensuring your confidentiality is safe with us.

HOW THE NABTA APP WORKS

EASY SET UP • Aya, our AI assistant will guide you through set- up, learning about your health goal.

LOG YOUR DATA • Track vital health signals to provide a view of your monthly menstrual cycle and ovulation calendar. You can add this manually or you can connect OvuSense, the vaginal thermometer to track your basal body temperature for accurate ovulation prediction.

ORDER AT HOME BLOOD TESTS • Aya will use your data to recommend any tests that will support diagnosis and help provide the right treatment advice.

GET PERSONALISED TIPS • Learn about relevant conditions and symptoms with evidence-based articles and daily tips.

FIND PRODUCTS & SERVICES • Access the Nabta Women’s Health Shop to find recommended products and services that will help you reach your health goal.

With over 500 touchpoints, our AI health assistant (Aya), and the ability to sync and analyse information from more than 300 wearable devices and apps including OvuSense vaginal thermometer, Apple Health, Garmin, and Fitbit, you won’t find a holistic health and cycle tracking app anywhere like us.

AND THERE’S MORE.

The Nabta app now offers support in four distinct areas – HEALTH, FERTILITY, PREGNANCY and MENOPAUSE – so you can stay on top of your fifth vital sign no matter what your age or stage!

For more information, please visit https://nabtahealth.com

FOLLOW our daily social updates in English and Arabic:
Instagram @nabtathealth
Twitter @nabtahealth
Pinterest @nabtahealth
Facebook.com/nabtahealth
Linkedin.com/nabtahealth

Your menstrual cycle is your 5th vital sign? As important for understanding your overall health as your heart rate, blood pressure, respiration rate and temperature?

SOMETHING IS WRONG
If you suffer with irregular cycles, heavy periods, painful periods, bleeding between periods, extreme PMS (known as Premenstrual Dysphoric Disorder), smelly discharge, itching, dryness – the list goes on.

GET DETAILED INSIGHTS YOU CAN TRUST
About your menstrual cycle in the context of your hormonal and overall health. The Nabta app combines the best of female, artificial and medical intelligence to help you understand your menstrual cycle in the context of your HEALTH GOALS.
• Want to know why your period is always late? We can help.
• Forced to take a sick day every month because of crippling period pain? We can help.
• Struggling to lose weight or keep it off? We can help.
• Worried you have PCOS? We can help.
• Trying to conceive for 6 months without success? We can help.

USE THE APP DAILY
The Nabta app is free and easy to use. It is designed to become a discreet, yet dependable part of your life, helping you manage your health with daily monitoring and advice. We use the most secure data encryption, ensuring your confidentiality is safe with us.

HOW THE NABTA APP WORKS

EASY SET UP • Aya, our AI assistant will guide you through set- up, learning about your health goal.

LOG YOUR DATA • Track vital health signals to provide a view of your monthly menstrual cycle and ovulation calendar. You can add this manually or you can connect OvuSense, the vaginal thermometer to track your basal body temperature for accurate ovulation prediction.

ORDER AT HOME BLOOD TESTS • Aya will use your data to recommend any tests that will support diagnosis and help provide the right treatment advice.

GET PERSONALISED TIPS • Learn about relevant conditions and symptoms with evidence-based articles and daily tips.

FIND PRODUCTS & SERVICES • Access the Nabta Women’s Health Shop to find recommended products and services that will help you reach your health goal.

With over 500 touchpoints, our AI health assistant (Aya), and the ability to sync and analyse information from more than 300 wearable devices and apps including OvuSense vaginal thermometer, Apple Health, Garmin, and Fitbit, you won’t find a holistic health and cycle tracking app anywhere like us.

AND THERE’S MORE.

The Nabta app now offers support in four distinct areas – HEALTH, FERTILITY, PREGNANCY and MENOPAUSE – so you can stay on top of your fifth vital sign no matter what your age or stage!

For more information, please visit https://nabtahealth.com
